README file for ocs2_sqp package 

0. this package requires external library installation hpipm and blasefo. All should reside in /opt/, which is the default place. 

BLASEFO: 
cd ~
git clone https://github.com/giaf/blasfeo
cd ~/blasefo
set BUILD_SHARED_LIBS to be ON & TARGET to be X64_AUTOMATIC in ~/blasefo/CMakeLists.txt
mkdir build 
cd ~/blasefo/build
cmake ..
make 
sudo make install 
installed in /opt/blasefo/, having folders /lib, /include, /cmake 

HPIPM: 
cd ~ 
git clone https://github.com/giaf/hpipm
cd ~/hpipm
set BUILD_SHARED_LIBS to be ON in cd ~/hpipm/CMakeLists.txt
mkdir build 
cd ~/hpipm/build
cmake ..
make 
sudo make install 
installed in /opt/hpipm/, having folders /lib, /include, /cmake 

you may need to set the variable 
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/opt/blasfeo/lib

Some useful commands for catkin: 
1. below is for different build types 
catkin config --cmake-args -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug
catkin config --cmake-args -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

2. below is for building tests 
catkin build --make-args tests -- my_package1 my_package2

3. One can use GDB to debug ros, add the following to the launch file 
      launch-prefix="gnome-terminal -- gdb -ex run --args"
      launch-prefix="gnome-terminal -- gdb -ex start --args"